content: Well, I didn't get too far setting this up. Went to Define User, then Vehicle, but Make only scrolls down to 'Nissan', no further. I guess I either have to buy a different car or a different app.

Awesome
Great app works well
Great app for HPDE enthusiasts.
I autocross. Using a Galaxy S9 & OBDLink LX, I get no useful data. The times are very wrong and the course map is useless. I suppose that I need a $150 external GPS.

Bought this app based on recommendation of two of my friends as we were at 
the track that day (they use this with no issue). They showed me how to set 
up the app so it would record my lap times. GPS etc was on but nothing was 
recorded on several track sessions. Basically just spent $10 on a 
completely useless app. Would appreciate some assistance as to what my 
problem is, maybe I'm doing something wrong.
Been using this app for quite some time now and I still love it as much as the first day I installed it!

Fantastic app! I used it for an oulton park trackday.  Just set up the driver details, downloaded the oulton park track, turned auto lock off on the phone and put it under the seat.  Simple! Got some great results back and made the trackday all the more enjoyable getting some results back.  Only limiting factor is my phones GPS only operating at 1hz, would get even better results with dedicated GPS plugged in, also if youre at a remote track there may be phone signal blackspots depending on your provider.  But for Â£6? Brilliant!
Great app when I get to go racing.
A wonderful tool for trackday fans. The most practical use of the smartphone since the browser.
Does the rookie app allow video overlay or do I need upgrade to petrol head

The UI is hell, it is not what an Android app should look like. When I was racing, I wasn't sure what is going on with the app. It showed me some lap times eventually, but some were wierd, i.e. too short. Also, I wasn't able to start video recording, neither from a GoPro, nor from the phone cam. For even a smaller price I'd expect a decent app that I can figure out how to use. I only installed it because it was a requirement for the racing event, and now I regret I did.

When I started using it I realized it's useless for data logging unless you have a fast GPS. If using a phone GPS all of the collected data will be coming in at a rate of 1hz which is not granular at all and makes it useless for analysis and video overlay. Other apps do not do this. I have emailed the developer asking for a refund, the initial response was very prompt, asking me for a transaction number. He replied saying google issues the refund. It's been over a month and no refund.
replyContent: According to Google's confirmation (we have made this available to the client for reference too), the refund has been issued on the 7th of June 2016. Please contact Google support in case you have problems accessing your account.

content: Used the new update.  Worked perfect on my Android S5
It's powerful but the UI is really confusing and hard to navigate.
Easy to use and great for improving one's personal best on the track.
I had to reinstall my phone- I can't see my upgrade to petrolhead I purchased through the app. How do I get my upgrade back??
replyContent: Please just load it again from LapTimer -> Administration -> Add-ons. You will not be charged again provided you use the same Google ID as before.

content: Everything you need for track days
App didn't work! Says "No fix" didn't pick up GPS signal. So disappointed as I didn't get to find out my lap time. This app sucks.
replyContent: In case LapTimer shows "No fix" it means your smartphone doesn't deliver valid GPS positions. This is nothing the app can change but requires your attention to mount the phone in a better position. Another potential reason is your device does not have a GPS sensor at all (some tablets come without). Please contact support at Harry@gps-laptimer.de

content: Works better than the other solutions out there. Simple to use interface

Harry has wonderful customer service and actually looks into troubleshooting his app when things get funky and weird. I appreciate his efforts in such a wonderful app and the constant updates!! Thank you Harry!
Can't wait for next track n test day @ brands Hatch with "Arcee "
Incredible app and developer. Basically implimented every request of users. Amazing commitment. Deserves to be a millionaire.
Loving the new Harrys Laptimer v18 for android. Answered all our prayers with the new "Gap" View mode!
Harry's lap-timer is the best track day timing app

Bugs have been fixed. Still lacks full functionality of the iPhone versions and the interface in clunky. You will have to search the forums to find out how to do stuff, but I finally got ODBII and video overlay working. :)
replyContent: LapTimer on Android follows the same edition portfolio like on iOS. In case you see something not documented correctly, please let us know. Petrolhead (the edition featuring video recording) is in development and will get available March 2014 (= this year). For more details, please check http://www.gps-laptimer.de/LapTimer_Products.html

content: Works best of any application I've downloaded. Maps are killer! A+

The only app to get for if track your car.  The bonus; this is the most well supported software you will ever own.  I have emailed Harry a number of times with questions or suggestions and he always responds promptly. I have seen update addressing an issue I had brought up days before.  I've been in software development for 20 years and you rarely see this level of dedication.
This is the best!  Such good video.

Since the android version became available this app has only improved.  Now with petrol head it kicks all other apps of this type to the curb.  I can run it on both my droid bionic and my Nexus 7.  A must have for track days.  Thanks Harry!
I've run most of the rest of the Android track timing apps and Harry's  is the best.
Done the in app upgrade to petrol head,  got a Google receipt,  but the app remains on rookie,  phone is a note 1,  sorted now just pressed upgrade twice and 2nd time it upgraded

This app is amazing for honing driving skills and repeatability. I just opted for the Petrolhead Add-On and couldn't be happier, now after a few data collection runs I can try to capture my best laps with HD video. Fantastic!
The best smartphone driving app available comes to Android!  Thank you Harry.

The Best Lapping Day App in the Play Store! I own both the Android and iPhone versions of this app and while the iPhone version is more mature, the Android version is rapidly catching up and already the best and most accurate in the store.  With the latest Petrolhead release, it has just gotten better, it is a shame I can't post a review on that app! Keep up the awesome work Harry, my Mercedes race car thanks you with my wallet! ;)

Simple to use, easily to load maps, accuracy is there. What can you still ask for? The next version if comes with Video Recording, I will still purchase. I have been using this apps since IOS all the way until Android. Will still stick with it.
Anxiously awaiting petrolhead version. Excited
replyContent: LT's functional breadth requires space. Problem for your installation is most probably you used the "Full reload" option in the Tracks area. Please use the "Update" function instead (adds missing data only). In case you have not recorded laps so far, please delete and install. I will add some housekeeping to 17.5. Hope you will enjoy LT on track.

content: Such a good app! Trackmaster has been buggy for a long time, and has not been fixed. The Bluetooth GPS in Trackmaster is busted. In Harry's it is great. Samples the Garmin GLO at 8-10hz. Can't wait for the fully featured app to come out.
Great but needs to catch up with the iOS version faster
Harry's does everything you could want in a cell phone PDR.
Looking forward to the extra features in 2014 :)

Multiple crashes on Android 4.3 nexus 4. Uninstalled, I'll stick with free racechrono for now. Maybe give it a try again in a few months.  (update) was going to give this a second shot at track last week but it's unusable because there is no vertical orientation view. With polarized sunglasses I cannot read the screen on my phone when it is horizontal. It needs to support both view modes.
replyContent: I sent a mail to you on your initial review but didn't receive a reply. In case you want to report what exactly happens, I have a chance to fix it. Actually I have not received any crash reports on the latest version so far. Whenever a problem without a workaround occurs, I try to fix it within 48 hours. So please get in touch ;-)

content: Very good app, but we need the petrol edition with video, it will be available for android?
replyContent: Harry's LapTimer Petrolhead Edition will be available in March 2014. I work on it all the time :-) There will be an upgrade path for the Rookie Edition too.

content: If you're not ready to spring $400+ on a dedicated lap timer, this app is the next best thing. Great features, plenty of data to review, and top-notch support from Harald. Recommended for any enthusiast that runs HPDE events and wants to track and improve lap times.

Own Harry's Lap Timer Grand Prix edition on iPhone and was worried when coming across to Android. However when they mentioned this software was being released on Android I jumped in and bought a note and now I am pleasantly surprised that Harry's Lap Timer works as good if not better on the larger format screen.  Thanks for bringing the best lap timer software on iPhone to Android. :)
great app for iphone sucks  for droid.  hung or rebooted my galaxy s3 every session yesterday.  extremely disappointed! !!!!!!!
replyContent: Please report back to Harry@gps-laptimer.de what exactly happened. Running in a sandbox LapTimer can definitively not reboot any smartphone (except Android itself is buggy). Maybe there is some configuration issue for your S3 we need to identify. Is your device rooted or runs some other GPS app in background? Thx.

content: Excellent app for weekend racers

I used this for the first time at an autocross today.   Not easy to use our intuitive.  Crashed my galaxy s4.  Had to take the battery out to unlock the phone.   Only got one of 8 runs logged. Using the timer became a hassle to deal with instead of an aid for a two driver car.
replyContent: Hi Rufus, In case LapTimer does not log your data, there is either a problem with the track setup, or with GPS quality. LapTimer needs to bridge reality to your smartphone and probably requires a different mounting or track setup. Please consider contacting us at Harry@gps-laptimer.de, I'm sure that can be solved.

content: If you are looking for an app that hook you up while you are on track, don't look further because HLT is the best in the market.   Very easy and informative app plus you can share your result directly to your Dropbox or by email.
Now works with VBox Sport on Samsung. Only portait mode required to work on tablets.
replyContent: LapTimer works very well with VBOX Sport (20 Hz) and has special support built in. In case you can't get it working, please contact us on Harry@gps-laptimer.de For Rookie we had a priority on landscape support as this orientation is the most frequent requested. Depending in the demand, views not avail in portrait currently, will be added later.

content: We need video and the additional features!!!!!
replyContent: Please rate Rookie here, not Petrolhead ;-) LapTimer Petrolhead will be ready Spring 2014 and bring all the cool features known from iOS. The full line up of LapTimer apps is available here: http://www.gps-laptimer.de/LapTimer_Products.html Your LapTimer Rookie will be fully upgradable to Petrolhead. Thanks!

content: difficult to use interface.....can't figure out how to stop the timer once it starts without exiting the program.....have used racechrono and trackmaster....have seen Harry's lap timer videos, and had hoped for more.    I've changed my star rating because the developer got right back to me with support!!!  I still am not fully satisfied with the user interface, but what excellent support!!
replyContent: When leaving the track back to the pits, you need to manually cancel the last lap (as it is void). To cancel, please press the large "Cancel" button in the Timer view (the one you will be in anyway). This will remove the last lap. Hope that helps, and please contact us directly at Harry@gps-laptimer.de in case you run into problems elsewhere.

content: Awesome app, clearly the best of its kind, but does use a fair bit of memory.

This is a great lap timer for android with a lot of features and a very active developer.   It works without a problem on my S4 with an OBDLink MX and a QStarz GPS.  Great for the track, autocross or just timing your drives to work.  Looking forward to the future versions so I can overlay telemetry onto my GoPro videos.
Great app but when do we get the Petrolhead edition?
replyContent: Please check http://www.gps-laptimer-forum.de/viewtopic.php?f=11&t=1537 for the Rookie announcements and next steps on Petrolhead. We work hard to add video support soon - at the same quality level seen on iOS. Please consider subscribing to the Announcements forum to get news pushed.

content: Brought it and used it yesterday for the first time at the race track. Used with Galaxy S4 and very happy with the results it put out. Would love to see the Petrolhead and Grand Prix edition out for it so I can get the full Harry's laptimer experience. Thankyou very much
replyContent: Thanks Thomas! I will release LapTimer Petrolhead as soon as possible - but it is some work to do. For LapTimer Rookie users, there will be Petrolhead upgrade available.

content: As everyone knows, Harry's Lap Timer has been a staple at any high performance driving event...that is if you were using iOS. In fact, I was considering buying a used, non-activated iPhone just for Harry's software. But thankfully, now I don't have to since it's available on Android.  I've tried other Android lap timers in the past, but nothing offered a full solution that combined both lap timing and OBD sensor readings (note: you need an OBD reader for that part to work) in one slick, sophisticated package.  Harry's Lap Timer is fill an important niche in the driving community that other apps haven't been able to match.
Not only does the app work flawlessly, but (unlike that other lap app) is actually supported by its creator. I used the beta and the support is fabulous. Harry's is THE laptimer for android.
Can't wait to use it.  Thanks for porting it!

Harry's lap timer has been on iOS for sometime, I've been waiting for the Android porting of this app for months, I can't wait to get out and use it, if it's anything like the iOS version it'll have been worth the wait.

Thanks for this, a great addition to the play market, been waiting for sometime now to get this app on the Android platform, this is by far the best mobile based lap timer ever, with support to OBD II and external GPS, big variety of export options, and hopefully soon GoPro connectivity (like the iOS version have), your track days and even fun runs and cruising sessions will be a happier place, thanks for a great app that we looked forward to and envied iOS users on it for so long :)
